.TH "omap4_cminst_wait_module_ready" 9 "omap4_cminst_wait_module_ready" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
omap4_cminst_wait_module_ready \- wait for a module to be in 'func' state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" omap4_cminst_wait_module_ready
.BI "(u8 part "  ","
.BI "s16 inst "  ","
.BI "u16 clkctrl_offs "  ","
.BI "u8 bit_shift "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "part" 12
PRCM partition ID that the CM_CLKCTRL register exists in
.IP "inst" 12
CM instance register offset (*_INST macro)
.IP "clkctrl_offs" 12
Module clock control register offset (*_CLKCTRL macro)
.IP "bit_shift" 12
bit shift for the register, ignored for OMAP4+
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Wait for the module IDLEST to be functional. If the idle state is in any
the non functional state (trans, idle or disabled), module and thus the
sysconfig cannot be accessed and will probably lead to an "imprecise
external abort"
